Package org.tensorflow.op.core

Class HistogramFixedWidth<U extends java.lang.Number>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.tensorflow.op.PrimitiveOp
      • org.tensorflow.op.core.HistogramFixedWidth<U>
  • Type Parameters:
    U - data type for out() output
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Op, Operand<U>
    @Operator
public final class HistogramFixedWidth<U extends java.lang.Number>
extends PrimitiveOp
implements Operand<U>
    Return histogram of values.

    Given the tensor `values`, this operation returns a rank 1 histogram counting the number of entries in `values` that fall into every bin. The bins are equal width and determined by the arguments `value_range` and `nbins`. 

    
 # Bins will be:  (-inf, 1), [1, 2), [2, 3), [3, 4), [4, inf)
 nbins = 5
 value_range = [0.0, 5.0]
 new_values = [-1.0, 0.0, 1.5, 2.0, 5.0, 15]
 
 with tf.get_default_session() as sess:
   hist = tf.histogram_fixed_width(new_values, value_range, nbins=5)
   variables.global_variables_initializer().run()
   sess.run(hist) => [2, 1, 1, 0, 2]
